**TASK 1.1 — Migrate to Open-Meteo as default data source**

Files to modify: `src/services/WeatherService.js`, `src/context/WeatherContext.js`

1. In `WeatherService.js`, add a new function `fetchOpenMeteo(lat, lon, units)`. Call `https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast` with params: `latitude={lat}&longitude={lon}&hourly=temperature_2m,apparent_temperature,precipitation_probability,precipitation,windspeed_10m,uv_index,cloudcover,visibility&daily=temperature_2m_max,temperature_2m_min,precipitation_probability_max,windspeed_10m_max,uv_index_max,sunrise,sunset&minutely_15=precipitation&current_weather=true&timezone=auto`. No API key required.
2. Map the Open-Meteo response to the existing WeatherContext data shape: `currently` maps from `current_weather` + first index of `hourly` arrays. `hourly.data` maps from `hourly` arrays zipped by index into objects with keys: `time`, `temperature`, `apparentTemperature`, `precipProbability`, `precipIntensity`, `windSpeed`, `uvIndex`, `cloudCover`, `visibility`, `summary`. `daily.data` maps from `daily` arrays. `minutely.data` maps from `minutely_15` arrays interpolated to per-minute entries.
3. In `WeatherContext.js`, replace the PirateWeather fetch call with `fetchOpenMeteo`. Keep the PirateWeather path in a fallback `try/catch` — if Open-Meteo fails, fall back to PirateWeather if user has a key stored.
4. Verify all existing components still receive correct data: `RainChart`, `HourlyScreen`, `SmartSummaryCard`, `AirQualityCard`, `GoldenHourCard`, `ActivityHub`. Fix any null/undefined access errors.

